The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Federer richest 
                                                                                                                                                                                                       Federer richest 
                  Roger Federer                     
	Paris/Madrid: Roger Federer has become the worlds richest tennis player, with career prize money earnings listed at a staggering $43.29 million.         
	Federers passage into the third round of the ATP Madrid Masters event on Wednesday saw the Swiss player edge past former No. 1 Pete Sampras of the US.         
	Federer will take his earnings to $43.5 million should he win in Spain. Sampras earned $43.27 million in his career.         
	Federer and Sampras stand almost $12 million clear of third-placed Andre Agassi. Current world No. 1 Rafael Nadal stands eighth on the list with $20.5 million in earnings.         
	On Wednesday, Federer returned after a five-week layoff and beat Radek Stepanek 6-3, 7-6 (6) in the second round of the Madrid Masters.         
	Novak Djokovic advanced after Victor Hanescu retired due to an apparent groin injury while trailing 7-6 (8), 6-7 (8), 1-3.         
	Indian ace Mahesh Bhupathi and Mark Knowles moved into the quarter finals when after Nadal and Carlos Moya pulled out due to a lower back injury to Nadal.         
	On Thursday, Britains Andy Murray reached the quarter finals after struggling past big-serving Croatian Marin Cilic 7-5, 7-6.         
	However, defending champion David Nalbandian of Argentina was easily dethroned 4-6, 2-6 by compatriot Juan Martin del Potro.         
	French world No. 16 Gilles Simon came back from two match points down to beat Robby Ginepri 6-7, 6-4, 7-6 in two-hours and 36-minutes.           (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                      
